cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about weakly-supervised semantic parsing using a neural parser-ranker system. The task involves generating logical forms from utterances using denotations as clues. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL), which is represented by cs.CL. The use of neural networks for this task also suggests the possibility of it being categorized under artificial intelligence (AI), which is represented by cs.AI. The paper also discusses a scheduled training procedure and the use of a neurally encoded lexicon, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL), represented by cs.LG. The task of semantic parsing also involves information retrieval (IR) and natural language understanding (NE), which are represented by cs.IR and cs.NE, respectively.
